Neurological improvement after cranioplasty - analysis by transcranial doppler ultrasonography. Cranioplasty can improve neurological status in patients with skull bone defects. The mechanism of postoperative improvement in neurologic status might be increased cerebral blood flow (CBF) velocity due to elimination of the effects of atmospheric pressure. Between May 2001 and June 2002, 13 patients (8 men and 5 women average age, 46 years